question: Would you do a ship for me please? I’m 19, I’m tall (like 5”10) I love music and painting and psychology. I’m really insecure about my weight lol. Ummmm I have black hair and blue eyes. Thank u!!!! Your blog is everything!!
answer:
~Don’t worry about it, darling. If anyone should apologize, it’s me because I’ve been to damn lazy too write anything (even though I asked for it). I love you so much and I hope you enjoy this ship!~

  I ship you with the little man-boy bean, Scott Favor from “My Own Private Idaho”.

·You met Scott when you were taking a stroll in downtown Portland during the summer, looking at all of the shops that lined the streets

·Scott was walking with Mike, chatting about recent clients and upcoming ones

·He spotted you looking at the display window of a clothing store, and he fell for you instantly

·He invited you to lunch and spent the time with introductions and playful banter

·After a while, Scott spent less time with Mike and the rest of the group and more time with you

·The two of you are constantly flirting with each other and very publicly displaying your affection for one another

·Scott is more than willing to take any chance he can get to do stuff that drives you wild, such as pinching or smacking your ass at any given time

·One time he even dared to run his fingers up your thighs and ended up fingering you through an entire meal in a well-populated restaurant

·He enjoys taking you to small, cozy restaurants and then going to a nearby bar

·He’s always up for taking you for a ride on his moped (and on him but either one works ya know)

·He’s very passionate in bed, using his skills from his former job

·Sometimes you get super kinky with all kinds of leather and chains

·You love to run your fingers through his thick hair, and he loves it as well

·Scott loves to come over to your place to hang out with you and your pets

·He is always very supportive of you and your looks, assuring you that you’re the most beautiful angel he’s ever seen

~Playlist~

  • “There Is A Light That Never Goes Out” by The Smiths
  • “Digital” by Joy Division
  • “Videogames” by Lana Del Rey
  • “Treat Me Like Fire” by Lion Babe
  • “Bad Kids” by Lady Gaga
  • “Get Down Make Love” by Queen

blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic
